edu.ucdavis.cstars.client.symbol

Class Symbol

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.gwt.core.client.JavaScriptObject
      • edu.ucdavis.cstars.client.symbol.Symbol
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    FillSymbol, Font, LineSymbol, MarkerSymbol, TextSymbol

    public class Symbol
extends com.google.gwt.core.client.JavaScriptObject
    Symbols are used to display points, lines, and polygons on the graphics layer. Symbol is the base symbol class and has no constructor. Instead, use the following: Points: SimpleMarkerSymbol, PictureMarkerSymbol Lines: SimpleLineSymbol, CartographicLineSymbol Polygons: SimpleFillSymbol, PictureFillSymbol Text: TextSymbol, Font
    Author:
    Justin Merz
